title: Red-Eyed Tree Frog
description: The red-eyed tree frog is a vibrant green frog with distinctive red eyes and blue and yellow stripes on its sides. It lives in rainforests in Central America.

title: American Bullfrog
description: The American bullfrog is a large, green frog native to North America. It is known for its loud croak and voracious appetite.

title: Glass Frog
description: The glass frog has translucent skin through which its internal organs can be seen. It inhabits tropical forests in Central and South America.

title: Tomato Frog
description: The tomato frog, named for its bright red or orange color, is native to Madagascar. It can secrete a sticky substance to deter predators.

title: African Clawed Frog
description: The African clawed frog is an aquatic frog native to sub-Saharan Africa. It has distinctive clawed toes on its hind legs.

title: Amazon Milk Frog
description: The Amazon milk frog, also known as the blue milk frog, is a large tree frog with distinctive blue and white coloring. It is found in the Amazon rainforest.

title: Pacman Frog
description: The Pacman frog, named for its large mouth and round body, is a terrestrial frog native to South America. It is known for its voracious appetite.

title: White's Tree Frog
description: White's tree frog, also known as the dumpy tree frog, is a large, green or blue-green frog native to Australia and New Guinea. It is known for its docile nature.

title: Wood Frog
description: The wood frog is a small, brown frog found in North America. It is known for its ability to survive being frozen during the winter.

title: Poison Dart Frog
description: The poison dart frog is known for its bright colors and toxic skin. It is found in Central and South America.
